<h2 id="terms">Terms<ac:structured-macro ac:name="anchor" ac:schema-version="1" ac:local-id="a6aa6f25-0bee-4a7f-929b-71fcb7eba592" ac:macro-id="d2cb5be1217ae6e086bc60005e9d27b7"><ac:parameter ac:name="">terms</ac:parameter></ac:structured-macro></h2>
<ul>
<li><p>page: a document which is fixed or constantly updated, such as company policy</p></li>
<li><p>blog: similar to page, but is time-based, generally not updated, such as news</p></li>
<li><p>space: a collection of pages or blogs. There are personal space and global space, the former has content only for oneself such as goals and notes, which are private, while the latter is used to share content among teams or the whole company, such as human resource.</p></li>
</ul>
